## Project Description

KnowledgeFlow AI is an AI-driven document intelligence solution that transforms uploaded documents into a searchable and interactive knowledge repository.

The platform allows users to upload PDF files and interact with their content through natural language queries. Uploaded documents are processed, segmented into meaningful chunks, embedded into a vector database, and leveraged by AI models to generate accurate, context-aware responses.

The primary goal of the project is to simplify access to information stored within large document collections. Rather than manually browsing extensive documents, users can quickly obtain relevant answers through conversational interactions.

This solution is valuable for organizations, teams, students, researchers, and anyone who frequently works with large volumes of document-based information.

---

## Approach

The application is built using a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) architecture.

### Workflow

1. User uploads a PDF document.
2. The backend extracts textual content from the uploaded file.
3. Extracted text is divided into smaller searchable chunks.
4. Embeddings are generated and stored within ChromaDB.
5. User submits a question in natural language.
6. The system retrieves the most relevant document context.
7. Gemini generates a contextual AI-powered response.

### Design Decisions

* Developed backend services using FastAPI for modularity and scalability.
* Chose semantic vector retrieval over traditional keyword-based search.
* Leveraged embeddings for improved contextual understanding of documents.
* Prioritized building a complete end-to-end AI workflow before focusing on UI enhancements.

